welcome_message_body: "Welcome to Garrison, a charming city known for its historical sites, stunning nature, and friendly locals. We're excited to have you here and encourage you to explore and experience all that our beautiful city has to offer!"

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at BWI airport serves all major airlines and offers a variety of amenities for travelers.

terminals.name: Concourse A
terminals.description: Concourse A is a satellite terminal that primarily serves Southwest Airlines and offers a variety of restaurants and shops for travelers.

terminals.name: Concourse B
terminals.description: Concourse B is a satellite terminal that primarily serves American Airlines and offers a variety of amenities for travelers.

terminals.name: Concourse C
terminals.description: Concourse C is a satellite terminal that primarily serves Delta Airlines and offers a variety of amenities for travelers.

terminals.name: Concourse D
terminals.description: Concourse D is a satellite terminal that primarily serves United Airlines and offers a variety of amenities for travelers.

wifi.note: WiFi is available throughout the airport with free basic access and paid premium options.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Tipton AAF Airport offers a variety of amenities for passengers, including dining options, gift shops, and rental car services.

terminals.name: Cargo Terminal
terminals.description: The cargo terminal at Tipton AAF Airport is equipped to handle a wide range of cargo, including perishable goods and oversized freight.

wifi.note: Passengers can enjoy complimentary WiFi throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Montgomery County Airport serves all commercial and private flights.

terminals.name: Private Terminal
terminals.description: The private terminal at Montgomery County Airport is exclusively for private and chartered flights.

wifi.note: Complimentary wifi is available throughout the airport.
